<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="365" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1189,1862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1189,1214]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Description.</emphasis>
Head narrower than pronotum, conically produced anteriorly (Plate II: A). Transition between vertex and face angular but not carinate (Plate II: A &amp; B). Ocelli on anterior margin of head closed to eye. Gena not incised and visible behind the eye in dorsal view. Pronotum widened posteriorly (Plate II: C). Forewing with reflexed veins to costa (Plate II: E). Profemur setal row AV with 
<number box="[881,950,1297,1321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17</number>
setae of nearly same length; IC row with 
<number box="[1422,1436,1297,1321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="6.0">6</number>
long setae of similar length; AM 
<number box="[537,546,1333,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
well developed (
<figureCitation box="[748,818,1333,1357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1499,1522]" captionTargetBox="[229,1343,411,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,373,1478]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: front femur, anterior view; B: left front tibia, upside view; C: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; D: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); E: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216756/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[804,818,1333,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Protibia dorsal setal formula 
<number box="[1203,1213,1333,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1230,1246,1333,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1265,1335,1333,1357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1499,1522]" captionTargetBox="[229,1343,411,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,373,1478]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: front femur, anterior view; B: left front tibia, upside view; C: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; D: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); E: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216756/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[1321,1335,1333,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B). 
<collectingCountry box="[1380,1436,1333,1357]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur setal formula 
<number box="[386,401,1369,1393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[418,433,1369,1393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[450,460,1369,1393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[478,547,1369,1393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1499,1522]" captionTargetBox="[229,1343,411,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,373,1478]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: front femur, anterior view; B: left front tibia, upside view; C: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; D: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); E: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216756/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[533,547,1369,1393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C). 
<collectingCountry box="[591,647,1369,1393]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia setal row AD: with approximately 
<number box="[1118,1146,1369,1393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="13.0">13</number>
long stout setae and 
<number box="[1394,1437,1369,1393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="0.0">0–5</number>
shorter stout setae between each long seta (
<figureCitation box="[641,708,1405,1429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1499,1522]" captionTargetBox="[229,1343,411,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,373,1478]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: front femur, anterior view; B: left front tibia, upside view; C: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; D: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); E: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216756/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[694,708,1405,1429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D); PD: with appproximately 
<number box="[1047,1075,1405,1429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="20.0">20</number>
macrosetae, slightly longer and narrower than those of AD, subequal to each other in length (
<figureCitation box="[837,903,1441,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1499,1522]" captionTargetBox="[229,1343,411,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,373,1478]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: front femur, anterior view; B: left front tibia, upside view; C: apex of hind femur, anterodorsal view; D: left hind tibia, anterior view (without AV); E: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216756/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[889,903,1441,1465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1189,1862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Male pygofer side without process (
<figureCitation box="[607,676,1477,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[213,1345,198,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; G: apex of aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216755/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[661,676,1477,1501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Valve triangular (
<figureCitation box="[916,981,1477,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,579,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1398,566,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xenovarta lui sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216754/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[970,981,1477,1501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Subgenital plate elongate, triangular with a row of marginal setae (
<figureCitation box="[507,577,1513,1537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[213,1345,198,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; G: apex of aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216755/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[562,577,1513,1537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Style with broad anterior part, subapical lobe discernable but not well developed, apophysis of style elongate (
<figureCitation box="[612,682,1549,1573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[213,1345,198,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; G: apex of aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216755/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[667,682,1549,1573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Connective fused with aedeagus, without paraphysis, its arms close together (
<figureCitation box="[322,394,1585,1609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[213,1345,198,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; G: apex of aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216755/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Figs 
<number box="[379,394,1585,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[424,439,1585,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
F). Aedeagus simple, with well developed dorsal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1108,1179,1585,1609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[213,1345,198,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; G: apex of aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216755/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Figs 
<number box="[1164,1179,1585,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[1210,1225,1585,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="365" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1189,1862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1621,1645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Remarks.</emphasis>
We place this genus in 
<taxonomicName box="[579,734,1621,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scaphytopiini">Scaphytopiini</taxonomicName>
based on the gena lacking an incision below the eye and being visible behind the eye in dorsal view. In the key to genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[914,1070,1657,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scaphytopiini">Scaphytopiini</taxonomicName>
of the Indian subcontinent by 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,600,1693,1717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. &amp; Anantha Murthy, H. V. (1999) A revision of the leafhopper tribe Scaphytopiini from India and Nepal (Insecta: Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae). Senckenbergiana Biologica, 79, 39 - 55." type="journal article">
Viraktamath &amp; Anantha Murthy (
<number box="[532,592,1693,1717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[613,753,1693,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aparaphysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[613,753,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Aparaphysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys out to 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath &amp; Anantha Murthy. It" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Anantha Murthy. It" box="[896,1436,1693,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sudhamruta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[896,1033,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Sudhamruta</emphasis>
Viraktamath &amp; Anantha Murthy. It
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[294,431,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sudhamruta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,431,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Sudhamruta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the connective without paraphysis (
<figureCitation box="[957,1030,1729,1753]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[213,1345,198,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; G: apex of aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216755/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Figs 
<number box="[1015,1030,1729,1753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[1061,1076,1729,1753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
F). This genus is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" box="[151,525,1765,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sikhamani" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Sikhamani</emphasis>
Viraktamath &amp; Webb
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having the connective without paraphysis and aedeagus without processes (
<figureCitation box="[273,345,1801,1825]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[213,1345,198,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aparaphysis lushuiiensis sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; G: apex of aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216755/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Figs 
<number box="[330,345,1801,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[375,390,1801,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
F). This genus is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Uhler" authorityName="Uhler" box="[748,961,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[748,890,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Scaphoideus</emphasis>
Uhler
</taxonomicName>
in coloration, wing venation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1286,1837,1862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1189,1862]" box="[199,1286,1837,1862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1837,1861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Etymology.</emphasis>
This genus is named for the connective lacking a paraphysis, the gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
